{
    "name": "Giant Crab",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Giant Crab",
            "type": "section",
            "text": "These skittering creatures are prized for their delicious meat, but their size makes them dangerous targets for harvesting. The statistics presented here represent giant crabs that live close to the water's surface. Crabs that live deeper underwater often exhibit more extreme adaptations to their environment. For example, crabs living in the depths where little light reaches them gain darkvision and cold resistance, and those adapted to the most hostile reaches of the deep sea can detect nearby creatures through subtle shifts in ocean currents.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 77",
                        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 77",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 276
                    },
                    "page": 77
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "Crab",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Crab Species",
                    "type": "section",
                    "text": "Crabs can be found along all the world\u2019s coastlines, ranging from relatively small creatures like the king crab or coconut crab to truly oversized monsters like the great reef crab, shark-eating crab, or lumbering shipwrecker crab.",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Monster Core 2",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 77",
                                "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 77",
                                "game-obj": "Sources",
                                "aonid": 276
                            },
                            "page": 77
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "related_creatures",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Related Creatures",
                        "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
                    }
                }
            ],
            "text": "Crabs are scavenging crustaceans known for their hard shells and iconic sideways gait. When confronted with threats from outside their species, most crabs prefer to flee, but when retreat isn't possible, they clamp on to their foes as tightly as they can.",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Monster Core 2",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Monster Core 2 pg. 77",
                        "alt": "Monster Core 2 pg. 77",
                        "game-obj": "Sources",
                        "aonid": 276
                    },
                    "page": 77
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
